---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Builders Map Africa">
  <main class="content-page">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">← Back to map</a>
    <section class="doc-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">About the project</p>
      <h1>Builders Map Africa</h1>
      <p>Builders Map Africa is an open-source map of Africa’s tech hubs, builder communities, startup spaces, innovation labs, accelerators, maker spaces, university labs, and ecosystem media.</p>
      <h2>Principles</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Open data first:</strong> Keep location data in readable GeoJSON files.</li>
        <li><strong>Community maintained:</strong> Let people suggest additions and corrections.</li>
        <li><strong>Verification matters:</strong> Every entry should have a clear status and last-verified date.</li>
        <li><strong>Simple before complex:</strong> No database or admin dashboard until the data volume demands it.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Roadmap</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Kenya MVP with map, filters, and contribution flow.</li>
        <li>Add Uganda, Rwanda, Tanzania, Nigeria, Ghana, South Africa, and Egypt.</li>
        <li>Add GitHub issue-based submissions and automated data validation.</li>
        <li>Add country pages and ecosystem reports.</li>
        <li>Add API and optional CMS/admin workflow.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
